PatternDescription: CORBA (REMOVED in JDK 11+)
Fix: Remove CORBA; replace with REST or RMI
RemediationDescription: Remove legacy tech; redesign to HTTP/REST or RMI.

PatternDescription: Java Transaction API (REMOVED in JDK 11+)
Fix: Use Jakarta Transactions or Spring Transaction Management
RemediationDescription: Move to Jakarta Transactions/Spring Tx; adjust imports/config.

PatternDescription: Internal APIs (CRITICAL - sun.* packages)
Fix: Replace sun.misc.BASE64Encoder with java.util.Base64 (available in Java 8+): Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(bytes)
RemediationDescription: Mechanical refactor; works on both JDK 8 and JDK 21.

PatternDescription: Internal APIs (CRITICAL - sun.* packages)
Fix: Replace sun.misc.BASE64Decoder with java.util.Base64 (available in Java 8+): Base64.getDecoder().decode(encoded)
RemediationDescription: Mechanical refactor; works on both JDK 8 and JDK 21.

PatternDescription: Internal APIs (CRITICAL - sun.* packages)
Fix: Use VarHandle or Atomic classes
RemediationDescription: Replace with VarHandle/Atomic or redesign for safe concurrency.

PatternDescription: Internal XML APIs
Fix: Use standard JDK XML APIs or Apache Xerces
RemediationDescription: Remove internal parser usage; depend on standard JAXP/Apache Xerces.

PatternDescription: Internal image APIs
Fix: Replace com.sun.image.codec.jpeg with javax.imageio.ImageIO (Java 8+).
RemediationDescription: Mechanical refactor to ImageIO; works on both JDK 8 and JDK 21.

PatternDescription: Deprecated Security & Cryptography
Fix: Use AES or modern algorithms: Cipher cipher = Cipher.getInstance("AES");
RemediationDescription: Adopt modern algorithms/protocols and update configs.

PatternDescription: Deprecated Security & Cryptography
Fix: Use AES or modern algorithms
RemediationDescription: Adopt modern algorithms/protocols and update configs.

PatternDescription: Weak hash algorithms
Fix: Replace with SHA-256: MessageDigest digest = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256");
RemediationDescription: Adopt modern algorithms/protocols and update configs.

PatternDescription: Old SSL/TLS versions
Fix: Use TLSv1.3 or higher
RemediationDescription: Adopt modern algorithms/protocols and update configs.

PatternDescription: Finalize methods (DEPRECATED in JDK 9 removal planned)
Fix: Remove finalize; use AutoCloseable and try-with-resources
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Object.finalize() calls
Fix: Remove finalize calls; rely on proper resource management
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Manual close() without try-with-resources
Fix: Use try-with-resources: try (BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"))) { /* ... */ }
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Old Date class usage
Fix: Use java.time.LocalDate: LocalDate date = LocalDate.now();
RemediationDescription: Use java.time and add generics; basic refactor then review.

PatternDescription: SimpleDateFormat (not thread-safe)
Fix: Use DateTimeFormatter: DateTimeFormatter formatter = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("yyyy-MM-dd");
RemediationDescription: Replace with DateTimeFormatter and thread-safe patterns.

PatternDescription: Calendar usage
Fix: Use LocalDateTime or ZonedDateTime
RemediationDescription: Use java.time and add generics; basic refactor then review.

PatternDescription: java.sql.Date/Time/Timestamp
Fix: Use java.time API
RemediationDescription: Use java.time and add generics; basic refactor then review.

PatternDescription: Raw types (pre-generics)
Fix: Use generics: List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
RemediationDescription: Introduce generics / use diamond operator; compile & fix warnings.

PatternDescription: Underscore as identifier (REMOVED in JDK 9+)
Fix: Rename variable
RemediationDescription: Rename `_` identifier to a valid name.

PatternDescription: Diamond operator missing
Fix: Add diamond operator: List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
RemediationDescription: Introduce generics / use diamond operator; compile & fix warnings.

PatternDescription: Thread.stop/suspend/resume (REMOVED)
Fix: Use ExecutorService or CompletableFuture
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Security Manager (DEPRECATED JDK 17 Â removed JDK 21)
Fix: Remove SecurityManager; use modern security frameworks
RemediationDescription: Remove SecurityManager usages; rely on modern security boundaries.

PatternDescription: Applet API (REMOVED in JDK 17+)
Fix: Remove Applet; migrate to web technologies
RemediationDescription: Remove legacy tech; redesign to HTTP/REST or web UI.

PatternDescription: Observable/Observer (DEPRECATED JDK 9)
Fix: Use java.beans.PropertyChangeSupport or reactive streams
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Runtime.runFinalizersOnExit (REMOVED)
Fix: Remove; use proper resource management
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Reflection on private fields (will fail with modules)
Fix: Use MethodHandles
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Class.newInstance() (DEPRECATED)
Fix: Replace Class.newInstance() with clazz.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance() (Java 8+).
RemediationDescription: Mechanical refactor; works on both JDK 8 and JDK 21.

PatternDescription: Package-level reflection
Fix: Avoid; use module-aware APIs
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Scriptlets (<% %>) increase risk during migration; prefer taglibs/EL.
Fix: Refactor scriptlets to JSTL/EL or migrate to Thymeleaf.
RemediationDescription: Refactor scriptlets to taglibs/EL or migrate views (e.g. Thymeleaf).

PatternDescription: sun.* usage inside JSP should be removed
Fix: Use supported JDK APIs (e.g. java.util.Base64).
RemediationDescription: Replace internal classes with supported JDK APIs.

PatternDescription: Nashorn engine removed after JDK 15.
Fix: Migrate to GraalVM JavaScript.
RemediationDescription: Move to GraalJS or other JS engine; change engine wiring.

PatternDescription: Strong encapsulation breaks deep reflection
Fix: Use public APIs / MethodHandles / --add-opens (last resort).
RemediationDescription: Refactor to supported APIs (try-with-resources/concurrency/public access).

PatternDescription: Log4j 1.x is EOL / incompatible.
Fix: Use SLF4J + Logback or Log4j2.
RemediationDescription: Migrate Log4j 1.x to SLF4J + Logback or Log4j2.

PatternDescription: SSLv3/TLSv1.0/1.1 insecure / disabled.
Fix: Use TLSv1.2+ (prefer TLSv1.3).
RemediationDescription: Adopt modern algorithms/protocols and update configs.

PatternDescription: MD5/SHA-1 usage is weak.
Fix: Use SHA-256 or better.
RemediationDescription: Adopt modern algorithms/protocols and update configs.

PatternDescription: JAXB removed from JDK 11+.
Fix: Dual-runtime: KEEP javax.xml.bind.* and add external JAXB (javax.*) dependencies (jaxb-api 2.3.x + jaxb-runtime 2.3.x) for JDK 11+.
RemediationDescription: Externalize JAXB to javax.* artifacts; no package rename; run tests on JDK 8 and JDK 21.

PatternDescription: JAX-WS removed from JDK 11+.
Fix: Dual-runtime: KEEP javax.xml.ws/javax.jws.* and add a javax.* JAX-WS implementation (Metro 2.3.x) for JDK 11+.
RemediationDescription: Externalize JAX-WS to javax.* artifacts; no package rename; run tests on JDK 8 and JDK 21.

PatternDescription: Replace with java.util.Base64.
Fix: Use java.util.Base64.
RemediationDescription: Mechanical code refactor to modern API (update imports/calls).

PatternDescription: CORBA removed.
Fix: Remove CORBA.
RemediationDescription: Remove legacy tech; redesign to HTTP/REST or RMI.

PatternDescription: Move javax.xml.bind.annotation.* to Jakarta.
Fix: Dual-runtime: KEEP javax.xml.bind.* and add external JAXB (javax.*) dependencies (jaxb-api 2.3.x + jaxb-runtime 2.3.x) for JDK 11+.
RemediationDescription: Externalize JAXB to javax.* artifacts; no package rename; run tests on JDK 8 and JDK 21.
